position_description : a post_doctoral research fellow position is available in the late stage pharmaceutical development department focusing on the impact of protein-protein interactions on the inter facial properties and dynamics of proteins . in particular , the impact of hydrophobic moieties as well as primary sequence on monoclonal antibody structure and properties will be examined through a variety of biophysical tools . protein biophamaceuticals come in contact with a variety of surfaces and interfaces ( eg air-water , solid-liquid , etc . ) . the effect of exposure to these interfaces on the proteins is not well understood . this project aims to utilize surface sensitive techniques ( eg qcm-d , bam , surface enhanced spectroscopy , etc . ) to examine the dynamics of protein adsorption and the effect of different surfaces / interfaces on the structure and conformation of the protein . a further objective of this project is to develop an understanding of the influence of protein-ion and protein-protein interactions as well as the effect of surfactants on the adsorption process and the properties of the adsorbed protein . the relative importance of protein-protein interactions in mediating surface-protein processes will be examined through the use of orthogonal methods such as dls , auc , etc . who you are requirements : a ph . d . in the field of biophysics ,
